"title": "4045: chaos",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4045",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A state of complete disorder or confusion. The first stage of creation where, having brought something out of nothing, God had not yet brought order to the universe. This primeval chaos, often symbolised by surging waters, threatens to disrupt God's order at any time. God sometimes allows a return to chaos as judgment.</p>\n<h2>God creates order out of chaos</h2>\n<h3>God creates something out of nothing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:1-Gen1:2\">GEN 1:1–1:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:9\">PSA 33:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps148:5-Ps148:6\">PSA 148:5–148:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:17\">ROM 4:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:3\">HEB 11:3</a></p>\n<h3>God brings order to his creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:12\">ISA 45:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:14-Gen1:19\">GEN 1:14–1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:8\">JOB 9:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:3\">PSA 8:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:13\">ISA 48:13</a></p>\n<h2>Chaos threatens God's order</h2>\n<h3>Life and order in creation must be sustained by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:29\">PSA 104:29</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:16-Col1:17\">COL 1:16–1:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job12:10\">JOB 12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job34:14-Job34:15\">JOB 34:14–34:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:5\">ISA 42:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:2-Heb1:3\">HEB 1:2–1:3</a></p>\n<h3>The raging sea as a symbol of chaos</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps46:2-Ps46:3\">PSA 46:2–46:3</a></strong> <em>The raging sea is a frequent symbol of the chaos from which the world was created and to which it could return. Yet those whose confidence is in the God who brought order out of chaos have nothing to fear</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:7-Ps104:9\">PSA 104:7–104:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:8\">EXO 15:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:2\">PSA 69:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:15\">PSA 69:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:16\">PSA 77:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:29\">PRO 8:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech10:11\">ZEC 10:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:23-Matt8:27\">MAT 8:23–8:27</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:36-Mark4:41\">MRK 4:36–4:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:22-Luke8:25\">LUK 8:22–8:25</a></p>\n<h3>Threatening nations are likened to the raging seas as bringers of chaos</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa17:12-Isa17:13\">ISA 17:12–17:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps46:6\">PSA 46:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:7\">JER 46:7</a></p>\n<h3>Spiritual and political chaos</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg17:6\">JDG 17:6</a></strong> <em>A period of anarchy, when no spiritual or political authority was recognised in Israel</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:14\">EPH 4:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:7\">GAL 1:7</a></p>\n<h2>God uses chaos as a judgment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa34:11\">ISA 34:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa24:1\">ISA 24:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa24:3-Isa24:4\">ISA 24:3–24:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa24:10-Isa24:12\">ISA 24:10–24:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa24:17-Isa24:21\">ISA 24:17–24:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa27:10\">ISA 27:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:14\">ISA 32:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:14-Zeph1:15\">ZEP 1:14–1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:15-Rev6:17\">REV 6:15–6:17</a></p>\n<h3>Floodwaters as a symbol of the chaos of judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah2:3\">JON 2:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:17\">GEN 6:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job20:28\">JOB 20:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job22:16\">JOB 22:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:7\">ISA 8:7</a></p>\n<h3>Panic and destruction characterise the chaos that follows judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:13\">ZEC 14:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:22\">JDG 7:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:20\">1SA 14:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:22-2Chr20:23\">2CH 20:22–20:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:2\">ISA 19:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek38:21\">EZK 38:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:22\">HAG 2:22</a></p>",
